Africa's lumber producers will convene in Angola to discuss new policies for imports and exports.
The African Timber Organization will host the 17th Africa Timber Conference in Cabinda, focusing on rainforest conservation.
Meanwhile, Malaysia and Austria plan to launch remote sensing satellites to monitor tropical forests.
Yunnan and Tanzania are also taking steps to protect their forest reserves.
Experts emphasize the importance of preserving biodiversity and combating deforestation to ensure the survival of endangered species and prevent desertification.
The efforts to safeguard these vital ecosystems are crucial for the future of our planet.
